    url: "https://english.sakshi.com/news/national/ban-5-medicines-ramdev-s-divya-pharmacy-uplifted-days-later-164556",
    title:
      "Ban on 5 Medicines of Ramdev\u2019s Divya Pharmacy Uplifted Days Later",
    text: "New Delhi: Days after asking the yoga guru Ramdev\u2019s Divya Pharmacy to halt the production of five medicines, the Uttarakhand Ayurveda and Unani Licensing Authority has revoked its ban. The new order has given permission to Divya Pharmacy to continue producing the five medicines.\n\nAfter repeated violation of the Drugs and Magic Remedies (Objectionable Advertisement) Act by Ramdev\u2019s Divya Pharmacy, the authorities had asked the company to stop the production of BPgrit, Madhugrit, Thyrogrit, Lipidom and Eyegrit Gold tablets. These drugs were being promoted as cures for these diseases blood pressure,diabetes, goitre, high cholesterol and glaucoma respectively.\n\nThe state drugs regulator for Ayurveda and Unani medicine had taken this action against the Divya Pharmacy following a complaint filed by Kerala-based ophthalmologist Dr KV Babu. The Kerala-based doctor had said the drugs for treatment of glaucoma advertised by Divya Pharmacy may pose a threat to eyesight.\n\nThe state drugs regulator for Ayurveda and Unani medicine issued an amended order on Saturday allowing the firm to resume production of these medicines. The state health authority GCN Jangpangi said it (earlier ban order) had been issued in haste. \u201cWe should have given the company time to explain its stand before issuing the order,\u201d Jangpangi said.\n\nMeanwhile, Patanjali issued a statement stating all the products and medicines made by Divya Pharmacy are according to the prescribed standards, fulfilling all statutory processes.\n\n\u201cWe are being attacked by those who run the business of confusion and fear in the world of medicine,\u201d the statement said. It also said there were clear signs of resistance from the \u201canti-Ayurveda drug mafia\u201d.\n\nAlso Read: Anushka Shetty London Shoot With Naveen Polishetty For 48th Film\n\n(With agencies inputs)",
