    url: "https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/black-country/dudley-bus-station-closed-fire-25503850",
    title: "Dudley bus station closed as fire rips through empty factory",
    text: 'Something went wrong, please try again later.\n\nInvalid email Something went wrong, please try again later.\n\nGet the latest Black Country news straight to your inbox\n\nPeople were forced to evacuate their homes as flames ripped through an empty factory in Dudley. More than 60 firefighters tackled the blaze, near to the town\'s bus station in Fisher Street.\n\nCrews from Dudley, Tipton, Oldbury, Haden Cross, Brierley Hill and Bilston arrived at the scene within five minutes of receiving a 999 call at 2.30am on Sunday, November 13. West Midlands Fire Service said a number of residents were evacuated as a "precaution" and were taken to a nearby fast food restaurant.\n\nThe town\'s bus station has been closed as a result of the fire, with people urged to check their routes before they travel." Fisher Street, Porters Field, St Joseph Street, Birmingham Street and Bourne Street are also currently closed at this time.\n\nREAD MORE: Man stabbed in street and another injured\n\nAt the height of the incident 10 fire engines, a 4x4 response vehicle and a hydraulic platform were in attendance. The fire service said crews "continue to make good progress".\n\nA spokesman added: "Our operations continue to scale down as we work closely with the Bus station operators, National Express, and the industrial premises owner. Please continue to avoid the area.\n\n"The following roads are currently closed- Fisher Street, Porters Field, St Joseph Street, Birmingham Street and Bourne Street. Fisher Road bus station also remains closed at this time, therefore we encourage you to review your route prior to commencing your journey."\n\nYou can find the latest details - including more pictures and video from the scene - on our live blog here.\n\nREAD NEXT:',
