    title:
      "'Female terrorist' kills six and leaves dozens injured in Istanbul bomb blast",
    text: '\u201cOur nation should make sure the perpetrators of the incident on Istiklal Avenue will be punished as they deserve,\u201d Recep Tayyip Erdogan told a news conference.\n\n\u201cIt would be wrong to say for sure this is terrorism. But the initial developments, initial information conveyed to us by the governor [suggests] there is a smell of terrorism here.\u201d\n\nHe did not specify any findings that could point to terrorism, but said \u201cinitial observations show that a woman played a role in the explosion\u201d.\n\nTurkey\'s vice president Fuat Oktay said: "We believe that it is a terrorist act carried out by an attacker, whom we consider to be a woman, exploding the bomb".\n\nJustice minister Bekir Bozdag said: "A woman had been sitting on one of the benches for more than 40 minutes and then she got up.\n\nOnly part of Istiklal Avenue was cordoned off on Sunday afternoon as nonchalant tourists and locals just 500 metres away still strolled with their shopping bags and weaved in and out of baklava stores.\n\nAmbulances rushed to the scene soon after the attack and helicopters were seen whizzing overhead.\n\nAuthorities did not immediately name the cause of the explosion. However, the blast evoked memories of the 2016 attack on the same street, when four people were killed and 36 injured in a suicide bombing linked to the Islamic State group.',
